Trying to get back on my Day Trade & Scalp game after crap entries on SPY yesterday - lowered the risk level, set up ToS Active Trader (yesterday) and adjusted numbers today.  Scalped AMD packs of 3 Puts at a time, sometimes 4x.  Upon entry, ToS AT triggered 3 OCO brackets: Close 2 Puts @ 10% profit, close 1 Put @ 25% profit, and Stop Loss @ 10%.  I adjusted the profit points based on the chart, s/r levels, and SPY action.  After hitting the first profit point i manually adjust the SL to 1% gain.  I need to get better at just letting the 25% runner run - If i had a 10% Trail Stop on those & just let them go, they would've run to that 13:30 time mark i have on the chart.  Solid day either way.

Hi there! Its been a long and confusing day.

England has re-entered a national lockdown, which means that most people will have to stay home until December 2nd. 

SUMMARY
From Thursday 5th November, people are to stay at home. 

 Exceptions include: 

small_blue_diamond Education
small_blue_diamond Working, if you cannot work from home
small_blue_diamond Exercise and recreation outdoors
small_blue_diamond Medical reasons
small_blue_diamond Shopping for food and essentials
small_blue_diamond Caring for others

Here is a summary of things that are changing, and things that are not changing:

small_blue_diamond Bars and restaurants will close, but takeaways can continue to operate - as in the spring lockdown
small_blue_diamond Shielding measures will not be re-introduced, but vulnerable people or those aged over 70 are told to be especially careful
small_blue_diamond Schools and universities will be kept open throughout this period, unlike in the lockdown earlier this year

Furlough

The furlough scheme has been extended, so if your place of work has been forced to close, then you can expect a continuation of government support.

Implementation

Parliament will debate and vote on these measures on Wednesday.
Johnson says the government in Westminster has updated the devolved administrations, and ministers "stand ready to work with them on plans for Christmas and beyond".

Outlook
'All the solutions are bad' - Prof. Chris Whitty 
Prof Whitty says "the idea that there is some perfect time to act is a complete misapprehension".

Hi there! Its been a long and confusing day.

England has re-entered a national lockdown, which means that most people will have to stay home until December 2nd. 

SUMMARY
From Thursday 5th November, people are to stay at home. 

 Exceptions include: 

small_blue_diamond Education
small_blue_diamond Working, if you cannot work from home
small_blue_diamond Exercise and recreation outdoors
small_blue_diamond Medical reasons
small_blue_diamond Shopping for food and essentials
small_blue_diamond Caring for others

Here is a summary of things that are changing, and things that are not changing:

small_blue_diamond Bars and restaurants will close, but takeaways can continue to operate - as in the spring lockdown
small_blue_diamond Shielding measures will not be re-introduced, but vulnerable people or those aged over 70 are told to be especially careful
small_blue_diamond Schools and universities will be kept open throughout this period, unlike in the lockdown earlier this year

Furlough

The furlough scheme has been extended, so if your place of work has been forced to close, then you can expect a continuation of government support.

Implementation

Parliament will debate and vote on these measures on Wednesday.
Johnson says the government in Westminster has updated the devolved administrations, and ministers "stand ready to work with them on plans for Christmas and beyond".

Outlook
'All the solutions are bad' - Prof. Chris Whitty 
Prof Whitty says "the idea that there is some perfect time to act is a complete misapprehension".
He says "all the solutions are bad" and the government is trying to go with "the least bad set of solutions".

After December 2nd, lockdown will end and the nation will return to the regional 'Tier' system that was in place prior to the new announcement.

Hopefully this has been a useful summary for you all, and everyone here at r/6thForm hopes that you stay safe in these uncertain times.

signifier: United States Steel Corporation Common Stock
content:
Expectancy tells us how a strategy will perform if we apply the same approach (average R-Multiple). R-Multiples let us see our average risk adjusted return. These tools work together to allow traders to analyze strategies and make adjustments. If you're only thinking about POP, you're missing an even more important part of the conversation. 
Expectancy = (Avg Win X Win Rate) - (Avg Loss X Loss Rate)
R-Multiple = Win Size / Risk 
-Erik

**AUD/USD** will most likely remain in its recent 0.68 0.70 trading range this week. Still, there is a risk the pair breaks lower towards 0.6660 if the course of the coronavirus pandemic darkens the U.S. and global economic outlook. The RBA's policy meeting on Tuesday is the local highlight. Expects no change in policy settings. The RBA is likely to reiterate that the economy has fared better than initially expected. Consumer confidence has rebounded particularly fast which bodes well for the outlook.
Could come under pressure this week because of concerns about a worsening of the diplomatic relationship between China and Australia. Weekend media reports suggested that the Australian government expects further retaliatory tariff increases from China after Prime Minister Scott Morrison's offer of a safe haven to Hong Kong citizens. Following increased tariffs on barley and beef, other products such as milk powder might be included. On Wednesday, the Australian Cabinet is expected to discuss a plan that could fast-track resettlement for Hong Kong citizens through the skilled visa program.

The ones who believed the rumor walked out the previous night and most haven‚Äôt returned. Then many of the remaining order selectors walked out after it was officially addressed last night. The management informed everyone that people had tested positive and then told them to go back to work. The people who tested positive worked for around a week shipping orders out to grocery stores and nothing is being done about it. If anyone was actually wondering about the timeline of div payouts

You need to buy the stock day before ex-div date.  
You can sell the stock on ex-div date.  
What happens is stocks takes 2 days to settle regardless of if you buy or sell on same day.  
The Record date (day after ex-div date) is when company makes note of who is eligible for the dividend.  
So if you own the stock on the day before ex div date then settlement happens 2 days after which would be the record date which makes you eligible for the div.

Levi was good to me because there were still shares available later in teh day when things settled more. for me, finding stocks with slightly larger short free float means I'm more likely to have that luxury to catch something more stable and ride it down. shorting is like going long, but with the added hassles of fees if you hold overnight, and no limit to what it could run up to, which is higher risk. margin calls suck!

signifier: Levi Strauss & Co Class A Common Stock
content: Looking at the levi chart, if I was still in, I'd be looking at that 15 level come monday, or lower.

the long green candle is several greens on the way up in rapid succession. it will hit several of them as resistance on the way down, often not fully bottoming out for days or weeks. think of the pattern as an umbrella, up the handle and dipping occasionally but only so far. you cna count on those dips but try to wait for teh bigger ones at those resistance levels on teh long greens at teh beginning. tha's how I do it anyway, self taught, for better or worse.

I did not play bonds specifically. Unless interest is going up they are not worth the effort to me.
I did for a while put my emergency fund in 12 month treasury notes and set them for renew because the interest was much higher by 20 times what a money market was. I bought 1k each auction which is 13 times a year.  That way every month I had 1k available if I did not renew.

When interest dropped I took off all auto renew and am letting the money go back into my checking, then moving it back to the market. That is how I am funding the market right now. If interest gets high enough again I may move 13k back to Treasuries again.

If interest does start going up, could be time to sell any good but time will tell.

If you plan on scalping for intra-day trading. I would recommend **keeping it simple.** I only use VWAP and 200EMA (sometimes, other times I don't use an indicator at all). I mainly trade on 1M but will use 5M or 4HR for swings or to confirm some S/R. 

But if you've been doing this for years I'm guessing it's been a decent strategy so far? It could potentially be the type of stocks you're trading?

If you're on a losing trend it should be extremely easy to find out why you're losing. When you say "looks like a good entry point" what does that look like for you? When you enter each position does it follow a criteria or trading strategy you utilize every time? 

What's the set up? 1M? 5M? What indicators do you use? How do you draw S/R? Again lots of different factors but it should be easy for you to figure out! Feel free to @ me if you have any specific questions. But if you can answer the questions above you should be able to figure it out on your own.

content: Yolo DAL puts paid off

Trying to get back on my Day Trade & Scalp game after crap entries on SPY yesterday - lowered the risk level, set up ToS Active Trader (yesterday) and adjusted numbers today.  Scalped AMD packs of 3 Puts at a time, sometimes 4x.  Upon entry, ToS AT triggered 3 OCO brackets: Close 2 Puts @ 10% profit, close 1 Put @ 25% profit, and Stop Loss @ 10%.  I adjusted the profit points based on the chart, s/r levels, and SPY action.  After hitting the first profit point i manually adjust the SL to 1% gain.  I need to get better at just letting the 25% runner run - If i had a 10% Trail Stop on those & just let them go, they would've run to that 13:30 time mark i have on the chart.  Solid day either way.

content: Yolo DAL puts paid off

Trying to get back on my Day Trade & Scalp game after crap entries on SPY yesterday - lowered the risk level, set up ToS Active Trader (yesterday) and adjusted numbers today.  Scalped AMD packs of 3 Puts at a time, sometimes 4x.  Upon entry, ToS AT triggered 3 OCO brackets: Close 2 Puts @ 10% profit, close 1 Put @ 25% profit, and Stop Loss @ 10%.  I adjusted the profit points based on the chart, s/r levels, and SPY action.  After hitting the first profit point i manually adjust the SL to 1% gain.  I need to get better at just letting the 25% runner run - If i had a 10% Trail Stop on those & just let them go, they would've run to that 13:30 time mark i have on the chart.  Solid day either way.

The  House of Representatives  postponed a vote on a  $2.2 trillion  coronavirus aid package as Democrats tried to find common ground with the  White House  on a bipartisan agreement, though they remained far apart on key issues.
Democratic aides said the delay was to allow the two sides one more day to keep talking before a vote. As written now, the legislation has no hope of advancing in the  GOP -controlled  Senate , but many centrist Democrats were eager to pass a new bill before they returned to campaigning in their home districts.
Treasury Secretary  Steven Mnuchin  and House Speaker  Nancy Pelosi  (D., Calif.) met Wednesday afternoon for 90 minutes and failed to reach an agreement.
"We found areas where we are seeking further clarification," Mrs. Pelosi said as she announced plans to hold a vote. "Our conversations will continue."
The updated legislation released earlier this week shaved the price tag of economic relief to  $2.2 trillion , compared with the  $3.5 trillion  bill the House passed in May.
"We still don't have an agreement, but we have more work to do," Mr. Mnuchin said after the meeting. "We're going to see where we end up."
Mr. Mnuchin and Mrs. Pelosi have made a late push to try to reach a coronavirus-relief deal before the election, despite skepticism on  Capitol Hill  that an agreement is possible at this stage. The House is slated to leave for a monthlong recess at the end of this week.

**Also will be entering puts as well as a long-term short position in Marriott International ($MAR). **

**Fundamentals: **Airbnb has already taken enough market share to justify a much lower forward P/E in the hotel industry. Millennials and Gen-Z are less attracted to the traditional hotel than any generation in history and this phenomenon is only accelerating. Airbnb is cheaper, usually nicer, and more convenient. The fundamental business of hotels is also worse than that of Airbnb. With hotels, if a customer dos not book a given room, that room doesn‚Äôt make money no matter what and thus loses profit on the wasted cost of the real estate. For Airbnb, if a customer doesn‚Äôt book a room Airbnb they incur no costs, and it‚Äôs this model plus the inherent profitability factor of Airbnb (prices are marked up comparative to hotels (hotels occupy a much bigger space)) that is drawing many entrepreneurs away from hotel enterprises and toward the modern Airbnb model. I expect this trend to continue as well and facilitate the growing market share of Airbnb over the next two decades.

*My opinion: hotels will reduce to <20% of the travel market by 2040. *
